    <main>
      <section class="section">
        <h2>About Jody</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">
          Jody uses an iPad and wants to take part in real conversations with the people around her.
          Our goal is to make that participation smoother, faster and less tiring.
        </p>

        <div class="stack">
          <!-- Block 1: situation -->
          <article class="card">
            <div class="pill">
              <span class="pill-dot"></span>
              Jody’s current situation
            </div>
            <h3>Communication challenges</h3>
            <p>
              Jody understands very well what is happening around her, but several factors make it hard
              for her to speak and be heard in time.
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>Speaking can be <span class="highlight">slow or tiring</span>, especially in noisy or stressful settings.</li>
              <li>Existing tablet tools require many precise taps, menus and navigation steps.</li>
              <li>She often depends on someone else to quickly say a short phrase or answer a question.</li>
            </ul>
          </article>

          <!-- Block 2: what we do -->
          <article class="card">
            <div class="pill">
              <span class="pill-dot"></span>
              What our solution aims to do
            </div>
            <h3>How we want to help</h3>
            <p>
              The solution focuses on supporting Jody’s voice, not replacing it.
              We want to make it easier for her to join and follow conversations.
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>Provide a <span class="highlight">simple and fast</span> way for Jody to be heard from her iPad.</li>
              <li>Make common daily phrases easy to access and play when she needs them.</li>
              <li>Reduce the effort needed to communicate so she can focus on the interaction itself.</li>
              <li>Increase her <span class="highlight">autonomy and social participation</span> in different environments.</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>
